===Etymology===
Possibly from the {{etyl|pox|de}} stem {{term|berl-|lang=pox}} / {{term|birl-||swamp|lang=pox}} + suffix {{term|-in|lang=pox}}. The place is first mentioned by this name in the late 12th century (as {{term|Berlyn|lang=gml}}). According to (incorrect) [[folk etymology]], the name is derived from the {{term|Bär||bear|lang=de}} that is the symbol of the city.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Standard New High German}} {{IPA|[bɛɐˈliːn]|[bɛʁˈliːn]|lang=de}},
